I proceeded to order a steam salmon fillet with shrimp and was informed that there was no salmon. My husband wanted a salmon burger so I questioned why the burger was available but not the fillet. The gentleman said that the patties are pre-made. I asked if they were 100% salmon and he responded yes. So we ordered a spicy salmon burger with no tomatoes, seasoned fries, a ten piece jumbo shrimp with potatoes and broccoli. We were told an estimated wait time of 25 minutes. Upon return, we were told another 7 minutes which turned into another 13 minutes. Our order was bagged up without even being asked if we wanted to put any condiments on our food items. To say the least, I was absolutely repulsed. The fries were over cooked and so hard they cut the top of my mouth. The “spicy” salmon sandwich was not prepared with any of the items listed on the menu but was dressed up in a brown piece of lettuce and a thick slice of tomato.
